{
  "texts": [
    "In recent years, the educational landscape has witnessed a surge of interest in leveraging artificial intelligence (AI) tutor bots to revolutionize personalized instruction across various academic disciplines, such as mathematics learning (Lee & Yeo, 2022), foreign language learning (Kohnke et al., 2023; Mageira et al., 2022), science learning (Cooper, 2023), programming learning (Ahmed & Hasnine, 2023; Dos Santos & Cury, 2023; Yilmaz & Yilmaz, 2023), business education (Chen et al., 2023), and public health (Fadhil & Gabrielli, 2017; Lee et al., 2022).",
    "These intelligent chatbots, exemplified by platforms like ChatGPT, have emerged as tools for tailoring educational experiences to the unique needs of individual learners.",
    "AI chatbots or bots enabled by ChatGPT are conversational agents that utilize AI technologies to engage in interactive and dynamic conversations with users.",
    "Chat-GPT is a language model developed by OpenAI that is trained on a vast amount of text data from the internet (Wu et al., 2023).",
    "Since ChatGPT became publicly accessible in November 2022, various claims have been made about its advanced AI capabilities."
  ]
}